'''Blue-listed''' species includes any indigenous species or subspecies ([[taxa]]) considered to be vulnerable in their locale. Vulnerable taxa are of special concern because of characteristics that make them particularly sensitive to human activities or natural events. Blue-listed taxa are at risk, but are not [[local extinction|extirpated]], [[endangered species|endangered]] or [[threatened species|threatened]].
