'''Entegrus Powerlines''' is an electric distributor located in [[southwestern Ontario]], Canada. The utility provides electrical supply to approximately 40,000 customers. Its service territory covers 96 square kilometers of urban areas, encompassed within a 5,000 square kilometer geographic area between [[Windsor, Ontario|Windsor]] (to the west), [[London, Ontario|London]] (to the east) and [[Sarnia]] (to the north). The Entegrus Powerlines service territory is more specifically described as encompassing the following:
==Formerly served towns== Those parts of the following former municipalities (including the former Police Village of Merlin) that the former dissolved public utilities served on December 31, 1997 * Town of [[Blenheim, Ontario|Blenheim]] * Town of [[Chatham-Kent|Bothwell]] * City of [[Chatham-Kent|Chatham]] * Town of [[Dresden, Ontario|Dresden]] * Village of [[Chatham-Kent|Erieau]] * [[Police Village]] of [[Merlin, Ontario|Merlin]] * Town of [[Ridgetown]] * Village of [[Thamesville]] * Town of [[Tilbury, Ontario|Tilbury]] * Town of [[Wallaceburg]], * Village of [[Wheatley, Ontario|Wheatley]], and * Part Lots 16 & 17, Concession A, Geographic Township of Raleigh, designated as Part 1, Reference Plan 24R 7195, Municipality of Chatham-Kent, and Part Lot 17, Concession A, Geographic Township of Raleigh, designated as Part 2, Reference Plan 7195, Municipality of Chatham-Kent as per Board Order RP-2003-0044, dated September 16, 2003. * The former Town of [[Strathroy-Caradoc|Strathroy]] as of December 31, 2000. * The former [[Police Village]] of [[Strathroy-Caradoc|Mount Brydges]] as of December 31, 2000. * The former Town of [[North Middlesex, Ontario|Parkhill]] as of December 31, 2000. * The Village of [[Dutton, Ontario|Dutton]] as of December 31, 1997, now within the Municipality of Dutton/Dunwich. * The Village of [[Newbury, Ontario|Newbury]] as of November 7, 1998.
