{{Infobox Protected area | name = Mein-ma-hla Kyun Wildlife Sanctuary | iucn_category = IV | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Burma | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within Burma | map_width = | location =[[Bogale Township]], [[Ayeyarwady Division]], {{flag|Burma}} | nearest_city = [[Bogale]] | coordinates = {{coord|16|1|08.06|N|95|17|55.18|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = {{convert|52.79|sqmi|km2|sigfig=3|order=flip}} | established = 1986 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = | embedded = {{Designation list | embed = yes | designation1 = Ramsar | designation1_offname = Meinmahla Kyun Wildlife Sanctuary | designation1_date = 3 January 2017 | designation1_number = 2280<ref>{{Cite web|title=Meinmahla Kyun Wildlife Sanctuary|website=[[Ramsar Convention|Ramsar]] Sites Information Service|url=https://rsis.ramsar.org/ris/2280|accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref>}} }}
'''Mein-ma-hla Kyun Wildlife Sanctuary''' ({{lang-my|မိန်းမလှကျွန်း တောရိုင်းတိရစ္ဆာန် ဘေးမဲ့တော}}) is a wetland reserve in [[Myanmar]]'s [[Ayeyarwady Delta]], located in [[Bogale Township]], [[Ayeyarwady Division]].<ref>Wogan, G.O., Win, H., Thin, T., Lwin, K.S., Shein, A.K., Kyi, S.W. and Tun, H. (2003). A new species of Bufo (Anura: Bufonidae) from Myanmar (Burma), and redescription of the little known species ''Bufo stuarti'' Smith 1929. Proceedings California Academy of Science 54: 141−153.</ref> It was established in 1986, is classified as a [[mangrove]] ecosystem reserve and occupies an area of {{convert|52.79|sqmi|km2|sigfig=3|order=flip}}.
''Mein-ma-hla'' means beautiful woman in Burmese.
==Flora and fauna== The [[protected area]] has a total of 29 mangrove tree species, [[saltwater crocodile]]s and a wide range of birds.<ref>[http://www.birdingmyanmar.com/south/meinmahla-kyun-wildlife-sanctuary.html www.birdingmyanmar.com]</ref>
