'''Plumber's putty''' is a type of [[putty]] used as a [[sealant]] in [[plumbing]]. It is a pliable substance used to make watertight seals around faucets and drains. The putty is a basic component of a plumber's toolkit and is often used when replacing plumbing fixtures.<ref>http://enlightenme.com/plumber-putty/</ref> Plumber's putty formulations vary but commonly include powdered [[clay]] and [[linseed oil]]. Other formulas use [[limestone]], [[talc]], or [[fish oil]]. [[RTV silicone]] or [[epoxy]] sealants may be used in place of putty.


